<subSubSection id="2FDE6573C0662B1BFF30F985E762F951" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="677B36F8C0662B1BFF30F985E204F93C" blockId="3.[151,1437,1316,1773]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="55B0EAEAC0662B1BFF30F985E22CF984" bold="true" box="[199,315,1567,1592]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species differs from other diadematoids found in 
<collectingCountry id="1FD37668C0662B1BFC2DF985E759F984" box="[986,1102,1567,1592]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
by having a very low test, conspicuously elongated, narrow genital plates, and spines in which the shaft is partially filled with a loose stereom meshwork.
</paragraph>
